<font color="#FF0000">ON YOUR BROTHER'S DEATH</font><br>
<tt>Thu Dec 18 17:02:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Regina,<br><br>
You are important though.  Please, don't feel guilty about your brother's death.  He died serving his country, trying in his own way to make this world better for all of us, but especially for those he loved--you!  He gave his supreme sacrifice not in vain, but so that we could continue with our lives.  We in this instance is very all-inclusive, and includes family, friends and, yes, the Vietnamese people too.<br><br>
I know that this is a time of hurt for you.  But you don't have to feel guilty.  I invite you to look at my web site, and read my essay, &quot;River of Life,&quot; to gain a better perspective of your brother's death.  (See www.sorcom.com/~searat).<br><br>
With the hope that you will find the courage to celebrate your brother's life, and the meaning of life, with those you love this Holiday Season,<br><br>
All Our Love,<br><br>
The Ratliff Family
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


